         <abstract>
            <p>In this paper, the asymptotic expansion of integrals of the form ∫&lt;sup&gt;∞&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;0&lt;/sub&gt; F(kr)f(k) dk is considered, as r tends to infinity, and where F(kr) are Bessel functions of the first and second kind, or functions closely related to these. Asymptotic expansions for several functions of this type are presented under suitable restrictions on f(k). The expansion given by Willis for Hankel transforms is seen to be valid under conditions of f(k) less restrictive than those imposed by that author.</p>
          </abstract>
